rk, you=E2=80=99ll quickly notice how collaborative of an enterprise innova=
tion is. They=E2=80=99re constantly talking to their peers, reading their p=
eers=E2=80=99 work, etc. And if you try to trace the history of a particula=
r technology or breakthrough, you=E2=80=99ll generally find tons of increme=
ntal improvements. There are a few notable, famous exceptions =E2=80=94 New=
ton inventing calculus all on his own, and so on. But these are very rare.=20
